---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="EduRankAI Meet · Video meetings, in-house" description="Full-scale video meetings built in-house — SFU + Mesh routing, generative AI audio codec, end-to-end encryption, 1,000-attendee webinars, on-prem mesh node for office-bandwidth savings. The whole stack documented.">

<style>
  body { background: #0a0a0c; color: #e8e8ee; }
  .mt-wrap { max-width: 1320px; margin: 0 auto; }

  .mt-hero { padding: 70px 5vw 60px; }
  .mt-eye { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; }
  .mt-title { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: clamp(46px, 8vw, 88px); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.035em; margin: 14px 0 18px; line-height: 0.96; max-width: 1000px; }
  .mt-title em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 500; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #67e8f9, #a78bfa); -webkit-background-clip: text; background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; }
  .mt-sub { font-size: 18px; color: #9aa6b6; max-width: 740px; line-height: 1.7; }

  .mt-cta-row { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 30px; }
  .mt-btn { background: #67e8f9; color: #04161b; padding: 14px 28px; border-radius: 10px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 800; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .mt-btn-ghost { background: transparent; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; color: #cfd6da; }

  .mt-strip { padding: 30px 5vw; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(150px, 1fr)); gap: 12px; border-top: 1px solid #1a1a25; border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a25; }
  .mt-stat-val { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600; color: #fff; line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .mt-stat-lbl { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 10.5px; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #9aa6b6; margin-top: 6px; font-weight: 700; }

  .mt-section { padding: 70px 5vw; border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a25; }
  .mt-section-eye { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; }
  .mt-section-h { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: clamp(30px, 5vw, 50px); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.025em; margin: 10px 0 16px; line-height: 1.1; }
  .mt-section-h em { color: #67e8f9; font-style: italic; font-weight: 500; }
  .mt-section-sub { font-size: 16px; color: #9aa6b6; max-width: 760px; line-height: 1.7; }

  .mt-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 14px; margin-top: 28px; }
  .mt-card { background: #11131a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 14px; padding: 22px; }
  .mt-card-icon { width: 42px; height: 42px; border-radius: 10px; background: rgba(103,232,249,0.15); color: #67e8f9; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .mt-card h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; margin: 8px 0 8px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.2; }
  .mt-card p { font-size: 14px; color: #9aa6b6; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }

  .mt-arch-diagram { background: #08080a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 14px; padding: 26px; margin-top: 22px; overflow-x: auto; }
  .mt-arch-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; min-width: 700px; }
  .mt-arch-table th { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #67e8f9; text-align: left; padding: 10px 14px; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a35; font-weight: 700; }
  .mt-arch-table td { padding: 12px 14px; border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a25; font-size: 13.5px; color: #cfd6da; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.6; }
  .mt-arch-table td:first-child { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; color: #a78bfa; font-weight: 700; white-space: nowrap; }
  .mt-arch-table td strong { color: #fff; font-weight: 700; }

  .mt-codeblock { background: #08080a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px 18px; font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: #86efac; line-height: 1.7; overflow-x: auto; margin: 16px 0; }
  .mt-codeblock .c { color: #6e6e78; font-style: italic; }
  .mt-codeblock .k { color: #c4b5fd; }
  .mt-codeblock .s { color: #fbbf24; }

  .mt-feature-list { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 10px; margin-top: 22px; }
  .mt-feature { display: flex; gap: 10px; align-items: flex-start; padding: 12px 16px; background: rgba(103,232,249,0.04); border-left: 2px solid #67e8f9; border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0; }
  .mt-feature-tick { color: #86efac; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }
  .mt-feature-text { font-size: 13.5px; color: #cfd6da; line-height: 1.55; }

  .mt-vs-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 22px; background: #11131a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; }
  .mt-vs-table th { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #67e8f9; padding: 12px 14px; text-align: left; background: #0a0a0c; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a35; font-weight: 700; }
  .mt-vs-table td { padding: 12px 14px; border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a25; font-size: 13.5px; color: #cfd6da; }
  .mt-vs-table td:first-child { color: #a78bfa; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-weight: 700; }
  .mt-tick { color: #86efac; font-weight: 700; }

  .mt-pricing-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 14px; margin-top: 28px; }
  .mt-price { background: #11131a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 16px; padding: 26px; }
  .mt-price.featured { border: 2px solid #67e8f9; }
  .mt-price-eye { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; }
  .mt-price-name { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin: 6px 0 12px; }
  .mt-price-amt { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 38px; font-weight: 600; color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .mt-price-per { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; color: #9aa6b6; }
  .mt-price ul { margin: 14px 0 0; padding: 0; list-style: none; }
  .mt-price li { padding: 6px 0; color: #cfd6da; font-size: 13.5px; display: flex; gap: 8px; align-items: flex-start; }
  .mt-price li::before { content: '+'; color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0; }
</style>

<main class="mt-wrap">

  <section class="mt-hero">
    <p class="mt-eye">EduRankAI · Meet</p>
    <h1 class="mt-title">Video meetings,<br/><em>in-house</em>.</h1>
    <p class="mt-sub">A full-scale video conferencing platform built end-to-end. SFU + on-prem Mesh routing, a generative AI audio codec that rebuilds speech over weak networks, real-time AV1 video, 1,000-attendee webinars, breakout rooms, whiteboarding, recording, transcription, end-to-end encryption. The whole stack documented here. Use it inside EduRankAI; license the SDK for your platform.</p>
    <div class="mt-cta-row">
      <a href="/portal/meet" class="mt-btn">Start a meeting &rarr;</a>
      <a href="#architecture" class="mt-btn mt-btn-ghost">View architecture</a>
      <a href="#sdk" class="mt-btn mt-btn-ghost">SDK + API</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-strip">
    <div><p class="mt-stat-val">1,000</p><p class="mt-stat-lbl">Attendees · webinar</p></div>
    <div><p class="mt-stat-val">SFU + Mesh</p><p class="mt-stat-lbl">Hybrid routing</p></div>
    <div><p class="mt-stat-val">&lt;120 ms</p><p class="mt-stat-lbl">P95 glass-to-glass</p></div>
    <div><p class="mt-stat-val">45%</p><p class="mt-stat-lbl">Packet-loss tolerance</p></div>
    <div><p class="mt-stat-val">E2E</p><p class="mt-stat-lbl">Encryption · default</p></div>
    <div><p class="mt-stat-val">8 codecs</p><p class="mt-stat-lbl">Including custom AI</p></div>
  </section>

  {/* CORE FEATURES */}
  <section class="mt-section">
    <p class="mt-section-eye">Core meeting features</p>
    <h2 class="mt-section-h">Every feature people <em>actually use</em>.</h2>
    <p class="mt-section-sub">We benchmarked against the dominant platforms and rebuilt every primitive in-house. Where they implement a feature behind a separate product, we ship it in the base tier.</p>

    <div class="mt-grid">
      <div class="mt-card">
        <div class="mt-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polygon points="23 7 16 12 23 17 23 7"/><rect x="1" y="5" width="15" height="14" rx="2"/></svg></div>
        <h3>HD video · AV1 + H.264</h3>
        <p>Up to 1080p at 30fps with automatic simulcast layers (90p / 360p / 720p / 1080p). Receiver picks the layer for its viewport. AV1 saves 30% bandwidth vs H.264 at the same quality.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-card">
        <div class="mt-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 1a3 3 0 0 0-3 3v8a3 3 0 0 0 6 0V4a3 3 0 0 0-3-3z"/><path d="M19 10v2a7 7 0 0 1-14 0v-2"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Generative AI audio codec</h3>
        <p>For weak networks: instead of compressing raw audio, the encoder transmits phoneme + prosody embeddings; the decoder rebuilds clean speech via a small on-device acoustic model. Intelligibility holds at 6&nbsp;kbps.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-card">
        <div class="mt-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Screen + region share</h3>
        <p>Share full screen, a specific window, a browser tab, or a free-draw region. High-frame-rate motion path (60fps) for code / animation share. Annotation overlay on top.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-card">
        <div class="mt-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Recording · cloud + local</h3>
        <p>Server-side recording: separate audio + video + screen-share tracks, plus a composited MP4. Local recording option for offline. Time-coded chapter markers. Auto-thumbnails.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-card">
        <div class="mt-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M9 18l6-6-6-6"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Breakout rooms</h3>
        <p>Up to 100 simultaneous breakouts. Host can auto-balance, manually assign, or self-select. Broadcast a message to all rooms. Pop-in to any room. Auto-return on timer.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-card">
        <div class="mt-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 3h18v18H3zM21 9H3M9 21V9"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Whiteboard</h3>
        <p>Shared infinite canvas. Pen, shapes, text, images, sticky notes, math typesetting (handwritten recognition). Each stroke is a data-channel packet — synced peer-to-peer.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-card">
        <div class="mt-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M21 11.5a8.38 8.38 0 0 1-.9 3.8 8.5 8.5 0 0 1-7.6 4.7 8.38 8.38 0 0 1-3.8-.9L3 21l1.9-5.7a8.38 8.38 0 0 1-.9-3.8 8.5 8.5 0 0 1 4.7-7.6 8.38 8.38 0 0 1 3.8-.9h.5a8.48 8.48 0 0 1 8 8v.5z"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Live captions · 32 languages</h3>
        <p>Real-time speech-to-text in 32 languages. Automatic translation between any two of them. Speaker-attributed captions. Captions are persisted to the transcript with timestamps.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-card">
        <div class="mt-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/><circle cx="19" cy="12" r="3"/><circle cx="5" cy="12" r="3"/></svg></div>
        <h3>AI meeting companion</h3>
        <p>Post-meeting summary, action items, decisions log, sentiment snapshot. Live transcript with speaker tags. Smart scheduling (find a slot across calendars). Suggested replies in team chat.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-card">
        <div class="mt-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Polls · Q&amp;A · reactions</h3>
        <p>Pre-scheduled or ad-hoc polls. Multi-choice, ranked, open text. Q&amp;A with upvotes. 16 reaction glyphs that float over the stage. Webinar attendees can &quot;raise hand&quot; queued by order.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-card">
        <div class="mt-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M2 12h20M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4-10z"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Background · blur, replace, virtual</h3>
        <p>Real-time segmentation runs on the device GPU via WebGL. Blur, replace with image, virtual background, or a custom-uploaded scene. Sub-frame latency at 720p.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-card">
        <div class="mt-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/></svg></div>
        <h3>End-to-end encryption</h3>
        <p>DTLS-SRTP per leg. For E2EE meetings: insertable streams + SFrame, keys never leave the client. Default on for 1:1 and small huddles; opt-in for larger meetings (where transcription and recording need server-side decode).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-card">
        <div class="mt-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"/><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Lobby · waiting room · host controls</h3>
        <p>Lobby with admission queue. Lock the meeting. Mute all / ask to mute. Remove participant. Co-host promotion. Spotlight a speaker. Disable chat. Disable rename. Audit log of all host actions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ARCHITECTURE */}
  <section class="mt-section" id="architecture">
    <p class="mt-section-eye">Architecture</p>
    <h2 class="mt-section-h">Under the <em>hood</em>.</h2>
    <p class="mt-section-sub">Hybrid SFU + Mesh routing with an on-prem option for office bandwidth savings. Open standards where they help interoperability (SIP, WebRTC); custom transport where they help reliability (UDP with FEC).</p>

    <div class="mt-arch-diagram">
      <table class="mt-arch-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Layer</th><th>EduRankAI Meet</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Media routing</td><td><strong>Hybrid SFU + MCU + Mesh.</strong> Default Selective Forwarding Unit (SFU) — each client uploads one stream, the SFU forwards per-receiver layer choices. MCU mixing on big webinars to save attendee CPU. Optional on-prem Mesh Node container — if 20 people in one office join, video stays on the LAN.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Transport</td><td><strong>UDP first, TCP / HTTPS fallback.</strong> Custom Forward Error Correction reconstructs streams under 45% packet loss. Adaptive bitrate with simulcast layers (90p / 360p / 720p / 1080p) chosen by receiver bandwidth.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Protocols</td><td><strong>WebRTC + SIP + H.323.</strong> Native standards for browser; SIP gateway for legacy room hardware (Polycom-style, Cisco-style); H.323 for older infrastructure. One-click join from any standards-compliant endpoint.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Video codecs</td><td><strong>AV1, H.264 SVC, VP9.</strong> AV1 preferred (30% bandwidth savings vs H.264). H.264 Scalable Video Coding for fan-out efficiency. Hardware acceleration when present (WebCodecs API).</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Audio codecs</td><td><strong>Opus + Custom Generative AI codec.</strong> Opus at 32–128 kbps for normal conditions; Generative AI codec drops to 6 kbps over weak networks by transmitting phoneme + prosody features and rebuilding speech on the receiver.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Noise + echo</td><td><strong>Hand-rolled DSP + DNN.</strong> RNNoise-class neural noise suppression. Acoustic echo cancellation. Speech enhancement (de-reverberation, equalisation). All on-device.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Background</td><td><strong>BodyPix-style segmentation</strong> on the device GPU via WebGL. Blur, replace, virtual background. Hand-rolled inference — no model download &gt; 2 MB.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Recording pipeline</td><td><strong>Per-track + composited.</strong> Server records each participant stream separately + a composited MP4 of the active speaker layout. Time-coded chapter markers. Resumable upload to durable storage.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Transcription + AI</td><td><strong>Streaming STT in 32 languages.</strong> Speaker-attributed transcript. Post-meeting summarisation + action-item extraction via the EduRankAI reasoning model. Smart scheduling across calendars.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Security · transport</td><td><strong>DTLS-SRTP.</strong> Every media leg encrypted between client and SFU.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Security · end-to-end</td><td><strong>Insertable Streams + SFrame.</strong> For E2EE mode, content keys never leave clients. Optional per-meeting. Default for 1:1 + small huddles.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Backend</td><td><strong>Go services + Rust media nodes.</strong> Microservices in Go for control plane (auth, scheduling, billing, recording). Rust for media nodes (SFU + Mesh). gRPC between control plane and media nodes. Postgres for state, Redis for ephemeral session data.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Infrastructure</td><td><strong>Multi-cloud + private edge.</strong> Control plane on Hetzner + OCI for cost. Media nodes on bare-metal + private data centres for latency. Anycast routing to nearest media POP. Optional self-hosted media nodes for compliance.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Capacity scaling</td><td><strong>SFU cascade for &gt; 250 attendees.</strong> Multiple SFUs federated; receivers connect to closest, edges relay between SFUs. Webinar mode tops out at 10,000 attendees.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* SDK + API */}
  <section class="mt-section" id="sdk">
    <p class="mt-section-eye">SDK + API</p>
    <h2 class="mt-section-h">Embed it in <em>your platform</em>.</h2>
    <p class="mt-section-sub">Same meeting engine — embeddable. Drop the SDK into your LMS, your hiring tool, your customer-support app. Or use the REST API to create meetings and webhooks from your backend.</p>

    <div class="mt-codeblock">
<span class="c">// 1. Embed the meeting iframe with one line</span>
<span class="c">// 1. Embed the meeting iframe with one line</span>
<span class="k">const</span> meeting = <span class="k">await</span> <span class="s">EduRankAI</span>.meet.<span class="s">create</span>(&#123;
  title: <span class="s">"Office hours"</span>,
  kind: <span class="s">"classroom"</span>,
  capacity: 250,
  features: &#123;
    record: <span class="k">true</span>,
    captions: <span class="k">true</span>,
    breakouts: <span class="k">true</span>,
    whiteboard: <span class="k">true</span>,
    e2ee: <span class="k">false</span>  <span class="c">{'// turn on for 1:1'}</span>
  &#125;,
  webhook: <span class="s">"https://yourapp.com/meet-events"</span>,
&#125;);
meeting.<span class="s">mount</span>(<span class="s">"#meet-container"</span>);
    </div>

    <div class="mt-codeblock">
<span class="c">// 2. Or use the REST API from your backend</span>
<span class="k">POST</span> <span class="s">"https://meet.edurankai.in/v1/meetings"</span>
Authorization: Bearer sk_live_...
&#123;
  <span class="s">"title"</span>: <span class="s">"Team standup"</span>,
  <span class="s">"scheduled_at"</span>: <span class="s">"2026-03-12T09:00:00Z"</span>,
  <span class="s">"invitees"</span>: [<span class="s">"alice@yourapp.com"</span>, <span class="s">"bob@yourapp.com"</span>]
&#125;
    </div>

    <div class="mt-feature-list">
      <div class="mt-feature"><span class="mt-feature-tick">+</span><span class="mt-feature-text"><strong>Embeddable iframe SDK</strong> — drop into any web app. CSS-customisable. White-label.</span></div>
      <div class="mt-feature"><span class="mt-feature-tick">+</span><span class="mt-feature-text"><strong>Native SDKs</strong> — iOS (Swift), Android (Kotlin), React, Vue, Flutter.</span></div>
      <div class="mt-feature"><span class="mt-feature-tick">+</span><span class="mt-feature-text"><strong>REST API</strong> — create, schedule, list, end, archive meetings.</span></div>
      <div class="mt-feature"><span class="mt-feature-tick">+</span><span class="mt-feature-text"><strong>Webhooks</strong> — start, end, participant_join, participant_leave, recording_ready, transcript_ready.</span></div>
      <div class="mt-feature"><span class="mt-feature-tick">+</span><span class="mt-feature-text"><strong>SIP gateway</strong> — dial in from a phone, or join from legacy room hardware.</span></div>
      <div class="mt-feature"><span class="mt-feature-tick">+</span><span class="mt-feature-text"><strong>Custom apps in-call</strong> — load your own React component into the right panel for polls, surveys, lesson plans.</span></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* CAPACITY + RELIABILITY */}
  <section class="mt-section">
    <p class="mt-section-eye">Capacity + reliability</p>
    <h2 class="mt-section-h">Smooth at <em>any size</em>.</h2>
    <p class="mt-section-sub">N-participant meetings shouldn't degrade as N grows. We use SFU cascade routing, simulcast layers, MCU fallback for huge webinars, and on-prem Mesh nodes for office bandwidth savings.</p>

    <div class="mt-feature-list" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(320px,1fr));">
      <div class="mt-feature"><span class="mt-feature-tick">+</span><span class="mt-feature-text"><strong>1 to 10 attendees</strong> — full SFU mesh, every client sees every other. Best for huddles, 1:1s, small workshops. P99 latency under 100 ms within a region.</span></div>
      <div class="mt-feature"><span class="mt-feature-tick">+</span><span class="mt-feature-text"><strong>10 to 250 attendees</strong> — SFU with simulcast layers. Receivers pick the layer matching their viewport size + bandwidth. Active-speaker layout. Best for classrooms, all-hands, team meetings.</span></div>
